From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 31 May 2026 14:26:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] irqchip/meson-gpio: enable the input glitch filter on every
 channel

The meson8-family gpio_intc has a per-channel input glitch filter
(REG_FILTER_SEL, 4 bits per channel) that requires the input to be
stable for N filter-clock cycles before an edge propagates to the GIC.
Mainline defines the register but never writes it, so the filter sits
at reset (0 = no debounce) and every contact glitch on a pin becomes
an interrupt. The stock Amlogic gpio_intc driver programmed this field
to its maximum (0x7) on every channel; the filter is what let stock
run a bouncy mechanical rotary encoder cleanly.

Program the same 0x7 in the meson8 set_type path so it applies to each
channel as it is configured. This rejects sub-window glitches at the
controller without throttling legitimate edges, which is what the
software report debounce in the rotary-encoder driver cannot do (that
only rate-limits reports). The two together reproduce the bounce
rejection stock relied on. Only the meson8 register layout carries
REG_FILTER_SEL; the s4 path uses a different register block and is
untouched.

The filter is harmless to the other consumers on this controller
(touch and proximity IRQs) - a few cycles of debounce on those lines
is at worst invisible. The exact time constant follows the
controller's default filter clock, which is the same clock stock's
0x7 ran against.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Pending
---
 drivers/irqchip/irq-meson-gpio.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/irqchip/irq-meson-gpio.c b/drivers/irqchip/irq-meson-gpio.c
--- a/drivers/irqchip/irq-meson-gpio.c
+++ b/drivers/irqchip/irq-meson-gpio.c
@@ -372,6 +372,11 @@
 	meson_gpio_irq_update_bits(ctl, REG_EDGE_POL,
 				   REG_EDGE_POL_MASK(params, idx), val);
 
+	/* max glitch filter; bare gpio_intc edges are unfiltered and a mechanical encoder bounces hard */
+	meson_gpio_irq_update_bits(ctl, REG_FILTER_SEL,
+				   0x7 << REG_FILTER_SEL_SHIFT(idx),
+				   0x7 << REG_FILTER_SEL_SHIFT(idx));
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
